-- Greece's Piraeus Bank swings to loss in Q3 on bad loan provisions
-- 
-- Tue Nov 25, 2014 10:34AM EST
-- None



ATHENS, Nov 25 (Reuters) - Greece's second-largest lender by assets, Piraeus Bank <BOPr.AT>, on Tuesday reported a loss in the third quarter after booking over 2 billion euros in charges for bad loanst.

Piraeus reported a net loss of 1.56 billion euros in the quarter, compared to a loss of 277 million euros in the year earlier period.